</h3><p class="sc-edLa-Dd hZPWCc pf-28_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">CPR is a lifesaving technique crucial in situations such as drowning, suffocation, or cardiac arrest. In paediatric cases, the stakes are incredibly high due to the vulnerability of children's health. Hygiene during CPR is paramount to prevent the transmission of infectious diseases between the rescuer and the child. Statistics indicate that adherence to hygiene protocols significantly reduces the risks of cross-contamination.
